{!</table>!}

@house_menu

- @house_simple_majority
- @house_super_majority
- @house_rep_lib_majority
- @house_defeat
- @house_lib_kingmaker
- @house_tie

@house_simple_majority
title: Republicans gain a majority in the House
subtitle: Republicans: [+ rep_r +] seats
view-if: house_majority = 2
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

The Republicans have secured a majority in the House of Representatives.

@house_super_majority
title: Republicans secure a supermajority
subtitle: Republicans: [+ rep_r +] seats
view-if: house_majority = 3
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

With two-thirds of the House, Republicans now wield veto-proof power.

@house_rep_lib_majority
title: Republicans and Liberal Republicans hold a working majority
subtitle: Republicans: [+ rep_r +] seats, Liberal Republicans: [+ lib_r +] seats
view-if: house_majority = 0 and rep_lib_working_majority = 1 and liberal_split = 1
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

Neither party holds an outright majority, but Republicans and Liberal Republicans together command enough seats to pass legislation if they can find common ground. Their cooperation will not come without a price.

@house_defeat
title: Republicans lose the House
subtitle: Republicans: [+ rep_r +] seats
view-if: house_majority = 0 and rep_lib_working_majority = 0 and dem_r > rep_r
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

The Democrats have taken control of the House of Representatives.

@house_lib_kingmaker
title: Liberal Republicans hold the balance of power
subtitle: Liberal Republicans: [+ lib_r +] seats
view-if: house_majority = 0 and rep_lib_working_majority = 0 and dem_r <= rep_r and liberal_split = 1
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

No party commands a majority. The Liberal Republicans find themselves in the position of kingmakers — their votes will determine whether Reconstruction legislation advances or stalls.

@house_tie
title: The House is tied!
subtitle: Both parties are neck and neck
view-if: rep_r = dem_r and house_majority = 0 and rep_lib_working_majority = 0
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 1

A tied House will cause major legislative deadlock in the months ahead.
